This topic informs on how to add more usability to a webpage. 

HTML Forms

Your first Web Form. How To Structure A Web Form.

1. Why are forms so important in web development?
  Forms are points of interaction for the user and server. It allows for things like templates to be updated, as
  well as enter data for processing and storage. It's important, so that the user may be able to make updates or input information to be processed
  on their end. 
2. When designing a form, what are some key things to keep in mind when it comes to user experience?
  Prioritizing and readability. Should be thinking about what comes first, next and last. Pay attention to not expose the full list at once, if 
  the form is long. Leave optional thing at the end. To name a few. 
3. List 5 form elements and explain their importance.
  <fieldset> Create groups of widgets that share the same purpose. 
  <legend> Label of the fieldset, explaining whats inside. 
  <label> Formal way to define a label for an HTML form widget. 


Learn JS

Introduction To Events.

1. How would you describe events to a non-technical friend?
  I would describe an event as being stuck at redlight. When the light turns green, it signals the event, allowing the driver to proceed through
  the light. 
2. When using the addEventListener() method, what 2 arguments will you need to provide?
  The name of the event, and a funciton to handle the even. 
3. Describe the event object. Why is the target within the event object useful?
  Its a parameter, automatically passed to event to event handlers to provide extra features and information. 
4. What is the difference between event bubbling and event capturing?
  Event bubling triggers on the inner most event of target element, then trickles to it's ancerstors. 
  Event capturing is when the event goes from the outermost element to the target element. 
